dashboardItems.text: *Service monitoring*
*SERVICE AVAILABILITY AND STOCKOUT*
*HIV TREATMENT COURSE STOCK STATUS OVERVIEW*

*DEFINITIONS:*
Closing balance = Opening balance + Received - Distributed - Redistributed - Discarded -->Automatically calculated indicator to count the remaining items at the end of the period
Stock on hand = physical stock count at the end of the period
Usable stock = Opening balance + received
Coverage time = Usable stock / Distributed + Discarded + Redistributed = no. of months

Stock discrepancy = Stock on hand - closing balance
If discrepancy = 0 and 9 --> Stock on hand = closing balance (green cell) - acceptable discrepancy -
If discrepancy < 0 --> closing balance > stock on hand (dark red cell)
If discrepancy > 9 --> closing balance < stock on hand (light red cell)
*TEST KIT STOCK STATUS OVERVIEW*
The gender category of ‘Other’ includes trans and gender diverse people who choose an identity other than male or female

*Linkage to prevention* measures the percentage of individuals linked to an HIV prevention intervention within 7 days after testing HIV-negative
*HIV retest coverage* measures the percentage of people testing HIV-negative and at elevated risk for HIV acquisition who tested again within a defined period after their previous HIV-negative test
The gender category of ‘Other’ includes trans and gender diverse people who choose an identity other than male or female

*SYPHILIS*
*Syphilis testing coverage (%)*: calculated over all the clients accessing HIV prevention services in the reporting period
*Syphilis test positivity (%)*: calculated amongst all clients tested for syphilis accessing HIV prevention services in the reporting period
*Syphilis treatment coverage (%)*: calculated amongst all clients who tested positive for syphilis in the reporting period

*GONORRHOEA*
*Gonorrhoea testing coverage (%)*: calculated over all the clients accessing HIV prevention services in the reporting period
*Gonorrhoea test positivity (%)*: calculated amongst all the clients tested for Gonorrhoea accessing HIV prevention services in the reporting period
*Gonorrhoea treatment coverage (%)*: calculated amongst all clients who tested positive for Gonorrhoea in the reporting period

*STI SYNDROME*
*Presence of STI syndrome (%)*: calculated over all the clients accessing HIV prevention services in the reporting period
*Repeat diagnosis of STI syndrome (%)*: calculated over all the clients diagnosed with a STI syndrome in the reporting period

The WHO 2021 guidelines for the management of STIs covers five syndromes: urethral discharge, vaginal discharge syndrome, lower abdominal pain, genital ulcer disease syndrome, and anorectal discharge.
The gender category of ‘Other’ includes trans and gender diverse people who choose an identity other than male or female
*Test coverage*: calculated over all the clients attending HIV prevention services in the reporting period

For syphilis, gonorrhoea and hepatitis B:
*Testing coverage (%)*: calculated amongst all the clients attending HIV prevention services in the reporting period
*Test positivity (%)*: calculated amongst all clients attending HIV prevention services in the reporting period who were tested
*Treatment coverage (%)*: calculated amongst all clients attending HIV prevention services  in the reporting period who tested positive

*Linkage to prevention* measures the percentage of individuals linked to an HIV prevention intervention within 7 days after testing HIV-negative

*HIV retest coverage* measures the percentage of people testing HIV-negative and at elevated risk for HIV acquisition who tested again within a defined period after their previous HIV-negative test
The category of other includes trans and gender diverse people who choose an identity other than male or female

*Treatment coverage (%)*: calculated amongst all clients attending HIV prevention services in the reporting period who tested positive

maps.description:
This visualisation is intended to facilitate the identification of population that has accesibility constraints to an HIV testing service.
Each point is an health facility which has been added a buffer of 5 km representing the accesibility to it.
A layer of population (the points in red) represent the estimated number of people living in that area (source: WorldPop / Google Earth Engine)
The health facility in blue are the ones offering the HIV testing service and with the cactchment area (5km) you can identify which population is covered or not by this service
